	pages = {e0183152},
	annote = {Summary
Shows that numbers of presences and frequencies of occurrences of species affect the species response curves and their niche attributes based on Huisman-Olff-Fresco models (HOF).Shows that flexible models (such as HOF models) can attribute different shapes of species response curves because of the structure of the data (nb of presences and frequencies) and not because of the ecological response. Maybe models that follow ecological theories should be preferred to flexible models.
